0:29Z", "closed_at": "2017-08-24T05:10:29Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "```shell\r\n# Google search for MRI .tgz brought to http://www.fmri-data-analysis.org/code\r\n# with boring list of urls to analysis code snippets and tarballs with data.\r\n# How to get that page useful content into a git/git-annex repository and be able\r\n# to update it if some erratum fixes get posted?\r\n\r\n# to get all text code snippets directly into git we use `--text-no-annex` switch\r\ndatalad create --text-no-annex handbook-fmri\r\ncd handbook-fmri\r\n\r\n# all urls of interest on that page seems to have `d=1` suffix, so we point crawler to  those\r\ndatalad crawl-init --save --template=simple_with_archives url=http://www.fmri-data-analysis.org/code 'a_href_match_=.*d=1$'\r\n\r\n# from now on crawler would know what to do\r\ndatalad crawl\r\n# you could now see code files from the page being added to git and \r\n# data files from tarballs to annex\r\nls\r\n# and upon rerunning the crawler, if nothing changed on the page, it should not do anything\r\ndatalad crawl\r\n```\r\n\r\n BTW, soon I would like to finish RF to meld `crawl-init` into `crawl --init`", "closed_by": {"login": "mih", "id": 136479, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEzNjQ3OQ==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/136479?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih", "html_url": "https://github.com/mih", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mih/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url":